# Force LF line endings on all text files in the repo. The repo stores
# LF; checkout produces LF regardless of platform `core.autocrlf` setting.
# This eliminates the CRLF noise from Windows-side Edit-tool operations
# that bit TASK-503/504/505 doc-syncs and required defensive sed-stripping
# every time a `.md` was touched.
*               text=auto eol=lf

# Husky hook scripts MUST be LF-ended or bash chokes on trailing \r.
# Kept explicit even with the project-wide rule above so the intent is
# obvious to readers.
.husky/*        text eol=lf
.husky/_/*      text eol=lf

# Common binary file types — be explicit so git's text-detection heuristics
# don't accidentally normalize them. `* text=auto` is usually right, but
# this is belt-and-suspenders for files we know are binary.
*.png           binary
*.jpg           binary
*.jpeg          binary
*.gif           binary
*.ico           binary
*.webp          binary
*.pdf           binary
*.woff          binary
*.woff2         binary
